FIGMA AUTO-LAYOUT TOKENS & SPACING RULES

(System of Proof UI — Production Standard)

1. BASE SPACING SCALE (FOUNDATION)
Spacing Unit

Base unit = 4px

All spacing must be a multiple of 4.
No exceptions.

Token Scale
Token	px	Usage
space-1	4px	Icon padding, tight inline gaps
space-2	8px	Badge padding, compact rows
space-3	12px	Form field vertical gap
space-4	16px	Default container padding
space-5	20px	Card internal spacing
space-6	24px	Section separation
space-8	32px	Major layout breaks
space-10	40px	Page section spacing
space-12	48px	Dashboard blocks
space-16	64px	Page-level separation

❌ Do not invent intermediate values
❌ Do not eyeball spacing

2. AUTO-LAYOUT RULES (NON-NEGOTIABLE)
Direction Rules

Vertical Auto-Layout → Pages, cards, forms, timelines

Horizontal Auto-Layout → Rows, tables, toolbars, badges

Padding Rules
Component	Padding
Page container	space-10
Card	space-5
Modal	space-6
Table row	space-3 vertical / space-4 horizontal
Badge	space-1 vertical / space-2 horizontal
Button	space-2 vertical / space-4 horizontal
Gap Rules
Context	Gap
Inline elements	space-2
Form fields	space-4
Card sections	space-5
Dashboard widgets	space-8
Timeline items	space-6
3. TYPOGRAPHY + AUTO-LAYOUT COUPLING

Typography spacing is not freeform. It is tied to layout.

Text Type	Bottom Margin
Page title (H1)	space-6
Section header (H2)	space-4
Subsection (H3)	space-3
Body text	space-2
Meta / labels	space-1

Auto-layout frames containing text must:

Hug contents vertically

Fill container horizontally

4. COMPONENT-LEVEL AUTO-LAYOUT SPECS
4.1 StatusBadge
Auto-layout: Horizontal
Padding: space-1 / space-2
Gap: space-1
Min height: 20px
Radius: 999px


Status color is semantic and locked.

4.2 QRCodeCard
Auto-layout: Vertical
Padding: space-5
Gap: space-4
Alignment: Center


Children:

QR image (fixed)

StatusBadge

Meta text (small)

4.3 EvidenceTimeline Item
Auto-layout: Vertical
Padding: space-4
Gap: space-2


Timeline container gap: space-6

4.4 Table / List Rows
Auto-layout: Horizontal
Padding: space-3 / space-4
Gap: space-4
Row height: Hug


Rows must stretch full width.
No card-style rows inside tables.

4.5 Form Group
Auto-layout: Vertical
Gap: space-2


Form sections separated by space-6.

5. PAGE-LEVEL LAYOUT RULES
5.1 Dashboard Pages
Vertical auto-layout
Padding: space-10
Gap: space-8


Each dashboard block:

Card
Padding: space-5
Gap: space-4

5.2 Detail Pages (Employee, Incident, Audit)
Header block
Gap: space-6

Content blocks
Gap: space-8


No masonry. No floating cards.
Linear, auditable structure only.

6. MODALS & DRAWERS
Modal
Padding: space-6
Gap: space-4
Max width: 640px

Side Drawer (Evidence Viewer)
Padding: space-6
Gap: space-5
Width: 420–480px


Drawer content scrolls. Header is fixed.

7. MOBILE AUTO-LAYOUT OVERRIDES
Mobile Page Container
Padding: space-4
Gap: space-6

Mobile Cards
Padding: space-4
Gap: space-3

Mobile Bottom Nav
Height: 56px
Icon gap: space-1

8. WHAT DESIGNERS ARE NOT ALLOWED TO DO

❌ No manual positioning
❌ No mixed spacing scales
❌ No visual padding adjustments
❌ No “optical alignment” hacks
❌ No breaking auto-layout for aesthetics

Everything must survive:

Dense data

Missing data

Audit exports

Mobile stress

9. HANDOFF CHECKLIST (FIGMA)

Before handoff, every frame must:

Use auto-layout (no absolute positioning)

Use spacing tokens only

Use semantic color styles

Hug contents where appropriate

Stretch where data grows

If not, it fails review.

FINAL CONFIRMATION

You now have:

A locked spacing system

Auto-layout rules that scale

Audit-safe visual hierarchy

Mobile-ready constraints

Direct mapping to CSS/Tailwind

This is enterprise-grade UI infrastructure, not a mockup.
